Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt:
(Cases 22CM872, 22CM723, 22CM474 are called at at 11:10 AM- by Zoom) Defendant Tranell Evans appears in custody via video conference from the Jail with Attorney Andrew Knaack. ADA Monica Fallon appears in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Warrants in 22CM723, 22CM474 are executed. Court orders the bonds in 22CM723 & 22CM474 previously ordered remain in effect. Defendant updates address and is eligible for Public Defender representation. 
22CM872- State requests $500 cash bond- flight risk. Defense requests signature bond- ties to the area. Court orders $250 cash bond with various conditions. 
Hearing in all cases: 11/29/2022 at 9:30 AM.

Warrant ordered but stayed until Monday 10/17/2022 at 12:00 PM

22CM723: Waives reading of the complaint and advised of charges and potential penalties. 

Both cases set for a Settlement Conference (by phone) with District Attorney's Office (715-839-4828) on 09/19/22 at 2pm
